	"VersionNumber": 1,
	"ResourceName": "duo_user_allowlist",
	"Description": "Provides a tuning control to suppress known-benign alerts for specific users (actor or target), either for a single alert name or globally, with optional expiry.\n\nFields: key,enabled,until_ymd,reason,owner\n\nKey format: \u003cnormalized_user\u003e|\u003calert_name_or_*\u003e (uses actor / target; until_ymd = YYYYMMDD; enabled = 1 or 0)\n\nkey: this field is the offending user and alert name\nenabled: this field allows you to specify for all alerts or just for a specific alert; 0 = no, 1 = yes\nuntil_ymd: this field allows you to specify a date to compare against; used for short term testing primarily\nreason: this field allows you to give a reason why this user was added to the allowlist\nowner: this field allows you to track who updated the allowlist\n\nExamples: This is currently what is in duo_user_allowlist.csv\nkey,enabled,until_ymd,reason,owner\nalice|Alert - Duo - High - Duo Admin Role Assigned to a User or Group,1,20251231,\"temporary exception for migration\"\nbob|*,1,,\"permanent allow across all alerts\"\n\nReference(s):\n\nUsage:\n$DUO_ALERT_BASE\n$DUO_ALERT_ENRICH\n$DUO_RISK_SCORE\n$DUO_TUNE_USER\n$DUO_ALERT_META",
